  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing food security in smallholder coffee farmers in Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is a stand-alone project, aimed at equipping marginalized farmers improve their farming techniques, diversifying into new high value crops and ensuring that they have access to farm input and markets for their produce.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is aimed at supporting 400 small holder farmers to diversify their farming into other high value crops that is nutritious and marketable. Through the production of other crops the families will be resilient and will spread the risks of a loss or reduced income from main cash crops such as coffee farming whose price has been quite volatile. The project will use farmer field school model where a select farmers will be trained on improved farming techniques and will be linked to markets for their produce. The families will also be linked to micro-finance institution to access credit for their farming. The project will also build the capacity of the farmer cooperatives to provide comprehensive agriculture services to the farmers &#x2013; from provision of inputs, to extension services and marketing.</narrative>
  </description>
